00:46:41.900 --> 00:46:43.142
AUDIENCE: Hi, Dr. Brown.

00:46:43.142 --> 00:46:44.790
I'm an allergy
sufferer, and I was

00:46:44.790 --> 00:46:47.480
wondering whether you have
any suggestions on how

00:46:47.480 --> 00:46:50.330
allergy sufferers
like myself and pets

00:46:50.330 --> 00:46:52.010
can more happily co-exist.

00:46:52.010 --> 00:46:52.760
CHRIS BROWN: Yeah.

00:46:52.760 --> 00:46:55.120
Really good question, and
probably a topic where there's

00:46:55.120 --> 00:46:56.890
a lot of misinformation.

00:46:56.890 --> 00:47:01.410
So a lot of people think that
when you are allergic to pets,

00:47:01.410 --> 00:47:02.880
you're allergic to the hair.

00:47:02.880 --> 00:47:06.480
And so the focus is always
on non-shedding cats

00:47:06.480 --> 00:47:08.040
and non-shedding dogs.

00:47:08.040 --> 00:47:10.190
That's actually not true.

00:47:10.190 --> 00:47:12.210
Allergy sufferers aren't
allergic to the hair.

00:47:12.210 --> 00:47:17.140
It's actually the dried
skin dander and also

00:47:17.140 --> 00:47:19.710
the saliva that
sits on the hair.

00:47:19.710 --> 00:47:22.629
So when pets groom themselves,
that sits on the fur,

00:47:22.629 --> 00:47:24.670
and then once it dries,
it flakes off and ends up

00:47:24.670 --> 00:47:26.920
in the air, we breathe
it in, and give off

00:47:26.920 --> 00:47:28.790
the signs of being allergic.

00:47:28.790 --> 00:47:32.690
So having a dog that
doesn't shed hair

00:47:32.690 --> 00:47:34.320
doesn't make too
much of a difference,

00:47:34.320 --> 00:47:38.330
but coincidentally, the
dogs that don't shed as much

00:47:38.330 --> 00:47:40.430
don't produce as
much of this protein.

00:47:40.430 --> 00:47:43.920
So the best way, if
you're looking for a dog,

00:47:43.920 --> 00:47:48.790
is to go and spend some time
in a room or outside-- probably

00:47:48.790 --> 00:47:51.550
better off-- with the puppies,
have them all over you,

00:47:51.550 --> 00:47:52.710
and see if you respond.

00:47:52.710 --> 00:47:55.030
And it's just a bit
of a trial and error.

00:47:55.030 --> 00:47:57.070
If you can find one
that doesn't cause

00:47:57.070 --> 00:48:02.190
you to be too allergic, then--
if you're having problems,

00:48:02.190 --> 00:48:04.280
wiping them down
with a damp cloth

00:48:04.280 --> 00:48:06.970
removes that allergen
off their coat.

00:48:06.970 --> 00:48:09.870
And so it makes you
less likely to respond.

00:48:09.870 --> 00:48:14.480
In terms of cats, Devon
Rex and the Rex breeds--

00:48:14.480 --> 00:48:17.950
the quite short-haired cats--
produce less of that protein

00:48:17.950 --> 00:48:19.560
as well.

00:48:19.560 --> 00:48:22.840
They're working madly to
produce an allergy-free cat,

00:48:22.840 --> 00:48:26.910
using genetic engineering,
and they're very close.

00:48:26.910 --> 00:48:29.080
And so that might help as well.

00:48:29.080 --> 00:48:34.950
But the funny thing
is that often, you

00:48:34.950 --> 00:48:40.320
can actually manage allergies
by simple exposure to animals.

00:48:40.320 --> 00:48:43.180
I'm actually
allergic to rabbits.

00:48:43.180 --> 00:48:44.990
[LAUGHTER]

00:48:44.990 --> 00:48:49.010
So if I don't see a
rabbit for six months

00:48:49.010 --> 00:48:51.410
or so in the vet clinic, the
next time I see a rabbit,

00:48:51.410 --> 00:48:52.775
I'll sneeze and have runny eyes.

00:48:52.775 --> 00:48:55.830
If I see, say, four
rabbits in a week,

00:48:55.830 --> 00:48:58.250
I'm not allergic to rabbits.

00:48:58.250 --> 00:49:02.820
You can almost self-cure
yourself by exposure.

00:49:02.820 --> 00:49:04.190
So it's one of those things.

00:49:04.190 --> 00:49:05.790
I'm not a human immunologist.

00:49:05.790 --> 00:49:09.070
So you can
de-sensitize yourself,

00:49:09.070 --> 00:49:12.450
but I don't know your exact form
of allergy to know for sure.

00:49:12.450 --> 00:49:17.360
But they're the basic principles
of allergies with pets.

00:49:17.360 --> 00:49:18.310
They're manageable.

